                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote type="miniature" subtype="historiated">
                                <p> There is a miniature of a seated king, identified as <q>CAROLUS
                                        MAGNUS REX</q>: King Charles the Great, i.e. Charlemagne, by
                                    a later hand on fol. <locus from="2r" to="2r">2r</locus>.</p>
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote type="initial" subtype="plain">
                                <p>There are three- to six-line initials in red ink on fol. <locus from="2r" to="2r">2r</locus>, fol. <locus from="2v" to="2v">2v</locus>, fol. <locus from="6r" to="6r">6r</locus>, fol.
                                        <locus from="10v" to="10v">10v</locus>, fol. <locus from="11r" to="11r">11r</locus> and fol. <locus from="27r" to="27r">27r</locus>.</p>
                            </decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>
                        <additions>Notes and ownership marks on the front and back flyleaves (fol.
                                <locus from="1v" to="1v">1v</locus> and fol. <locus from="36r" to="36r">36r</locus>) as well as on fol. <locus from="1r" to="1r">1r</locus> by <name type="person" key="JacVas001">Jacobus
